title: LAI Reading Group
text: Lancaster AI (LAI) reading group is a weekly reading group focusing on topics related to AI, including but not limited to: diffusion models, information geometry, stochastic optimisation, geometric deep learning. It will be more tutorial-styled, instead of seminar-styled, tailored more towards people (postgraduate students, postdoc, faculty members) who wish to learn more about the recent developments of AI. This reading group ties in nicely with the Prob_AI Hub.
